Property.preferredDefinition: The type of a material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes. This includes particular types of cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory substances.

ConceptualDomain.preferredDefinition: attributes of a patient's laboratory sample, including the source, condition, and fixative.

ValueDomain.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products._Something distinguishable as an identifiable class based on common qualities.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A viscid fluid secreted by the synovial membrane, serving as a lubricant.

Concepts.definition: A viscid fluid secreted by the synovial membrane, serving as a lubricant.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The watery fluid in the mouth made by the salivary glands. Saliva moistens food to help digestion and it helps protect the mouth against infections.

Concepts.definition: The watery fluid in the mouth made by the salivary glands. Saliva moistens food to help digestion and it helps protect the mouth against infections.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The fluid that is excreted by the kidneys.  It is stored in the bladder and discharged through the urethra.

Concepts.definition: The fluid that is excreted by the kidneys.  It is stored in the bladder and discharged through the urethra.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The material discharged from the bowel during defecation.  It consists of undigested food, intestinal mucus, epithelial cells, and bacteria.

Concepts.definition: The material discharged from the bowel during defecation.  It consists of undigested food, intestinal mucus, epithelial cells, and bacteria.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A sample comprised of cells collected from the inside of a subject's cheek.

Concepts.definition: A sample comprised of cells collected from the inside of a subject's cheek.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Tissue composed of specialized cells that are organized as a definite organ, situated along the course of lymphatic vessels, and consisting of an outer cortical and an inner medullary part. The lymph nodes are the main source of lymphocytes of the peripheral blood and serve as a defense mechanism by removing noxious agents, such as bacteria and toxins, and probably play a role in antibody production.

Concepts.definition: Tissue composed of specialized cells that are organized as a definite organ, situated along the course of lymphatic vessels, and consisting of an outer cortical and an inner medullary part. The lymph nodes are the main source of lymphocytes of the peripheral blood and serve as a defense mechanism by removing noxious agents, such as bacteria and toxins, and probably play a role in antibody production.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Tissue composed of three layers- epidermis, dermis and subcutis which protect underlying muscles and organs. Skin is used for insulation, vitamin D production, sensation, and excretion through sweat.

Concepts.definition: Tissue composed of three layers- epidermis, dermis and subcutis which protect underlying muscles and organs. Skin is used for insulation, vitamin D production, sensation, and excretion through sweat.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Fluid introduced into, and collected from, the lungs by a bronchoalveolar lavage procedure.

Concepts.definition: Fluid introduced into, and collected from, the lungs by a bronchoalveolar lavage procedure.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A specimen of bone marrow tissue obtained by using a relatively large diameter needle designed to acquire a core specimen.

Concepts.definition: A specimen of bone marrow tissue obtained by using a relatively large diameter needle designed to acquire a core specimen.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A specimen prepared by spreading cells from bone marrow aspirate thinly on a glass slide for microscopic examination. The study of bone marrow smears is routinely used for the investigation, diagnosis, and staging of hematopoietic disorders.

Concepts.definition: A specimen prepared by spreading cells from bone marrow aspirate thinly on a glass slide for microscopic examination. The study of bone marrow smears is routinely used for the investigation, diagnosis, and staging of hematopoietic disorders.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Aspirate from bone marrow.

Concepts.definition: Aspirate from bone marrow.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The middle layer of an anticoagulated blood specimen following separation by centrifugation. It contains most of the white blood cells and platelets.

Concepts.definition: The middle layer of an anticoagulated blood specimen following separation by centrifugation. It contains most of the white blood cells and platelets.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Autologous or allogeneic T-lymphocytes that are engineered to contain a chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) that specifically targets a particular antigen.

Concepts.definition: Autologous or allogeneic T-lymphocytes that are engineered to contain a chimeric antigen receptor (CAR) that specifically targets a particular antigen.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: DNA found in blood plasma and other bodily fluids that is not associated with cells.

Concepts.definition: DNA found in blood plasma and other bodily fluids that is not associated with cells.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The liquid lying above a liquid, solid or semi-solid residue, which is separated by crystallization, precipitation or centrifugation of a cerebrospinal fluid sample.

Concepts.definition: The liquid lying above a liquid, solid or semi-solid residue, which is separated by crystallization, precipitation or centrifugation of a cerebrospinal fluid sample.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A metastatic cancer cell found in the peripheral blood.

Concepts.definition: A metastatic cancer cell found in the peripheral blood.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Neoplasm-derived DNA found in blood plasma and other bodily fluids that is not associated with cells.

Concepts.definition: Neoplasm-derived DNA found in blood plasma and other bodily fluids that is not associated with cells.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A microscope slide prepared by depositing cells directly onto a slide by centrifugation. The cytocentrifuge spins at an angle, at low speeds, allowing the cells to adhere to the slide in a monolayer format.

Concepts.definition: A microscope slide prepared by depositing cells directly onto a slide by centrifugation. The cytocentrifuge spins at an angle, at low speeds, allowing the cells to adhere to the slide in a monolayer format.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A long linear double-stranded polymer formed from nucleotides attached to a deoxyribose backbone and found in the nucleus of a cell; associated with the transmission of genetic information.

Concepts.definition: A long linear double-stranded polymer formed from nucleotides attached to a deoxyribose backbone and found in the nucleus of a cell; associated with the transmission of genetic information.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A formalin-fixed, paraffin-embedded tissue sample that has been cut on a microtome so that it rolls up on itself.

Concepts.definition: A formalin-fixed, paraffin-embedded tissue sample that has been cut on a microtome so that it rolls up on itself.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The removal of tissue or fluid with a thin needle for examination under a microscope.

Concepts.definition: The removal of tissue or fluid with a thin needle for examination under a microscope.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A slide on which a fixed specimen has been mounted.

Concepts.definition: A slide on which a fixed specimen has been mounted.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Tissue that is not frozen or embedded in preservatives

Concepts.definition: Tissue that is not frozen or embedded in preservatives

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A tissue sample that has been frozen prior to analysis.

Concepts.definition: A tissue sample that has been frozen prior to analysis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A thin slice of tissue cut from a frozen specimen, often used for rapid microscopic diagnosis.

Concepts.definition: A thin slice of tissue cut from a frozen specimen, often used for rapid microscopic diagnosis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The DNA in germ cells (egg and sperm cells that join to form an embryo). Germline DNA is the source of DNA for all other cells in the body.

Concepts.definition: The DNA in germ cells (egg or sperm).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Type of substance that may be described as a linear sequence of nucleosides typically linked through phosphate esters.

Concepts.definition: Type of substance that may be described as a linear sequence of nucleosides typically linked through phosphate esters.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A peripheral blood cell with a single nucleus. This category includes lymphocytes and monocytes.

Concepts.definition: A peripheral blood cell with a single nucleus. This category includes lymphocytes and monocytes.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: An immature (progenitor) cell circulating in the peripheral blood.  It has the capacity for replication and differentiation to mature blood cells.

Concepts.definition: An immature (progenitor) cell circulating in the peripheral blood.  It has the capacity for replication and differentiation to mature blood cells.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A compound of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another.

Concepts.definition: A compound of two or more amino acids where the alpha carboxyl group of one is bound to the alpha amino group of another.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The small amount of fluid that is generated in the abdominal cavity to lubricate the peritoneum.

Concepts.definition: The small amount of fluid that is generated in the abdominal cavity to lubricate the peritoneum.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Plasma is the fluid (noncellular) portion of the circulating blood, as distinguished from the serum that is the fluid portion of the blood obtained by removal of the fibrin clot and blood cells after coagulation.

Concepts.definition: Plasma is the fluid (noncellular) portion of the circulating blood, as distinguished from the serum that is the fluid portion of the blood obtained by removal of the fibrin clot and blood cells after coagulation.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: No value exists.

Concepts.definition: No value exists.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The liquid lying above a liquid, solid or semi-solid residue, which is separated by crystallization, precipitation or centrifugation of a pleural fluid sample.

Concepts.definition: The liquid lying above a liquid, solid or semi-solid residue, which is separated by crystallization, precipitation or centrifugation of a pleural fluid sample.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The fluid that is ordinarily present in the pleural space. It allows for normal movement of the lungs during respiration.

Concepts.definition: The fluid that is ordinarily present in the pleural space. It allows for normal movement of the lungs during respiration.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Single-stranded long chain of nucleotides containing ribose. It is the end product of DNA transcription by the enzyme RNA polymerase. It is essential in protein synthesis.

Concepts.definition: Single-stranded long chain of nucleotides containing ribose. It is the end product of DNA transcription by the enzyme RNA polymerase. It is essential in protein synthesis.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The clear portion of the blood that remains after the removal of the blood cells and the clotting proteins.

Concepts.definition: The clear portion of the blood that remains after the removal of the blood cells and the clotting proteins.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Blood that has not been separated into its various components; blood that has not been modified except for the addition of an anticoagulant.

Concepts.definition: Blood that has not been separated into its various components; blood that has not been modified except for the addition of an anticoagulant.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A sample of blood applied in a thin film to a microscope slide for study under a microscope.

Concepts.definition: A sample of blood applied in a thin film to a microscope slide for study under a microscope.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A biospecimen consisting of fluid obtained from within the pericardial sac.

Concepts.definition: A biospecimen consisting of fluid obtained from within the pericardial sac.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A cylindrical piece of tissue, such as that resulting from a core biopsy.

Concepts.definition: A cylindrical piece of tissue, such as that resulting from a core biopsy.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A specimen of cerebrospinal fluid.

Concepts.definition: A specimen of cerebrospinal fluid.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The RNA in germ cells (egg or sperm).

Concepts.definition: The RNA in germ cells (egg or sperm).

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The nucleic acid in germ cells (egg or sperm).

Concepts.definition: The nucleic acid in germ cells (egg or sperm).

Concepts.definition: A tissue section that has been fixed with formalin and embedded in a paraffin block.

Concepts.definition: Leukocytes harvested from peripheral blood by leukapheresis.

Concepts.definition: The cell-free liquid obtained from bronchoalveolar lavage.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: Cells harvested from the bronchi and alveoli by lavage.

Concepts.definition: Cells harvested from the bronchi and alveoli by lavage.

Concepts.definition: A biological sample containing mononuclear cells isolated from the bone marrow of an experimental subject.

Concepts.definition: The cell-free liquid obtained while harvesting cells from bone marrow.

Concepts.definition: Any cell specimen isolated from cerebrospinal fluid.

Concepts.definition: A sample that has been fixed with formalin and embedded in a paraffin block.

Concepts.definition: The cell-free liquid obtained from peripheral blood mononuclear cell harvesting.

Concepts.definition: Cells harvested from the peritoneum.

Concepts.definition: Cells harvested from the pleura, usually by lavage.

Concepts.definition: The proteins released from a cell following membrane lysis.
